	<img class="leftFloat" src="../Media/Unit01_Write_e6.jpg" mode="1" id="1003"  /><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q1" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: This pattern is true for almost all other equipment.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q2" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: For example, the percentage of boys with computers in their bedroom is almost twice the percentage for girls.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q3" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: Almost 1 in 2 children have one.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q4" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: It is clear that a large proportion of all children, just over 50 per cent, have some kind of equipment in their bedroom and that the percentage is considerably higher for boys.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q5" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: The television is closely followed by games consoles in popularity.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q6" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: The only exception is video cassette recorders, which are slightly more common in girls' bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q7" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: A third of boys own such consoles compared to only a fifth of girls.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q8" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: A closer look at the figures shows that the most common appliance found in children's bedrooms is the television set.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q9" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: However, these are far more popular with boys than with girls.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q10" type="droptarget" />: The bar chart shows the percentages of girls and boys with home entertainment equipment in their bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q11" type="droptarget" /><font color="#000000">: We might also wonder what effect this has on their social development.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></font></p><p align="left"><font color="#0000ff"><input id="q12" type="droptarget" />: We could infer from these figures that children today spend a lot of their free time in their bedrooms.<font color="#0000ff"></font></font></p><p align="left"><font size="2"></font></p>
